---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro"
import Header from "../components/Header.astro"
---

<Layout
  title="Terms of Service — Should I Go Outside?"
  description="Terms of Service for Should I Go Outside? — the weather app that answers the only question that matters."
>
  <Header />
  <main class="page">
    <div class="card">
      <a href="/" class="brutal-btn brutal-btn--sm btn-back">← Back to home</a>

      <h1 class="title">Terms of Service</h1>
      <p class="meta">
        Effective date: March 12, 2026 &nbsp;·&nbsp; shouldigooutside.now
      </p>

      <p class="intro">
        Before you use Should I Go Outside? (the app or this website), please
        read these terms. By using the app, you're agreeing to them.
      </p>

      <section class="section">
        <h2 class="section-heading">1. Acceptance of Terms</h2>
        <p>
          By downloading, installing, or using the Should I Go Outside? app or
          visiting shouldigooutside.now, you agree to be bound by these Terms of
          Service. If you don't agree, please don't use the app or this website.
        </p>
        <p>
          These terms apply to all users of the app and website, wherever you
          are in the world.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <h2 class="section-heading">2. What the App Does</h2>
        <p>
          Should I Go Outside? is a free app that looks at weather data for your
          location and gives you a simple, opinionated answer to one question:
          should you go outside right now?
        </p>
        <p>
          The app gives you a <strong>recommendation</strong>, not a
          professional weather forecast.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>The app is free to use with no in-app purchases.</li>
          <li>No account creation is required to use the app.</li>
          <li>
            Weather data is sourced from third-party providers (see Section 7).
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <h2 class="section-heading">3. No Warranty — Provided As-Is</h2>
        <p>
          Should I Go Outside? is provided <strong>"as-is"</strong> without any warranties,
          express or implied. We make no guarantees about the accuracy, completeness,
          or timeliness of the weather data or recommendations shown in the app.
        </p>
        <p>
          The app pulls data from third-party weather services, and we can't
          control the accuracy of that data.
        </p>
        <p>
          We don't warrant that the app will be available at all times, free
          from bugs, or suitable for any particular purpose.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <h2 class="section-heading">4. Limitation of Liability</h2>
        <p>
          To the fullest extent permitted by law, Should I Go Outside? and its
          creator (Jordon de Hoog) will not be liable for any damages arising
          from your use of the app or website, including but not limited to
          decisions you made based on the app's recommendations. Please use
          common sense alongside the app.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <h2 class="section-heading">5. Acceptable Use</h2>
        <p>Please don't misuse the app. You agree not to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            Attempt to reverse-engineer, scrape, or hack the app or website.
          </li>
          <li>
            Use the app in any way that could harm other users or the service
            itself.
          </li>
          <li>
            Use automated bots or scrapers to extract data from the app or
            website without permission.
          </li>
          <li>Use the app for any unlawful purpose.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Be respectful and use the app as intended.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <h2 class="section-heading">6. Intellectual Property</h2>
        <p>
          Everything in the Should I Go Outside? app and on this website (the
          name, logo, design, copy, and code) belongs to Should I Go Outside?
          (Jordon de Hoog) unless otherwise noted.
        </p>
        <p>
          You're welcome to share screenshots, link to the site, and talk about
          the app. You just can't copy or redistribute our brand, design, or
          content as your own.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <h2 class="section-heading">7. Third-Party Services</h2>
        <p>The app relies on external services to function, including:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Weather APIs</strong> for current and forecast weather data for
            your location.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Firebase</strong> for backend infrastructure and app functionality.
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          These third-party services have their own terms of service and privacy
          policies, which we don't control. We're not responsible for how those
          services handle your data or for any outages they may cause.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <h2 class="section-heading">8. Termination</h2>
        <p>
          We reserve the right to suspend or terminate access to the app or
          website at any time, for any reason, with or without notice. This
          includes (but isn't limited to) situations where these terms are being
          violated.
        </p>
        <p>
          Since no account is required, this mostly means we could block access
          from specific sources if needed.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <h2 class="section-heading">9. Changes to These Terms</h2>
        <p>
          We may update these Terms of Service from time to time. When we do,
          we'll update the effective date at the top of this page. Continued use
          of the app or website after changes are posted means you accept the
          updated terms.
        </p>
        <p>We'll keep terms changes reasonable and clearly communicated.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <h2 class="section-heading">10. Governing Law</h2>
        <p>
          These terms are intended to be read internationally and in good faith.
        </p>
        <p>
          If any provision of these terms is found to be unenforceable, the
          remaining provisions will still apply.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="section">
        <h2 class="section-heading">11. Contact</h2>
        <p>Questions about these terms? Get in touch:</p>
        <div class="contact-card">
          <p><strong>Jordon de Hoog</strong></p>
          <p>
            <a href="mailto:contact@toebeans.life" class="contact-link"
              >contact@toebeans.life</a
            >
          </p>
        </div>
        <p>We'll do our best to respond promptly.</p>
      </section>

      <a href="/" class="brutal-btn brutal-btn--sm btn-back">← Back to home</a>
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>

<style>
  .page {
    min-height: 100vh;
    background-color: var(--color-bg);
    padding: 3rem 1.5rem 4rem;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    align-items: flex-start;
  }

  .card {
    background-color: var(--color-surface);
    border: var(--border-width) solid var(--color-outline);
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-offset-lg) var(--shadow-offset-lg) 0 0
      var(--color-shadow);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    padding: 3rem 3.5rem;
    max-width: 720px;
    width: 100%;
    transform: rotate(-0.5deg);
  }

  .btn-back {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    background-color: var(--color-primary);
    padding: 0.5rem 1rem;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
  }

  .title {
    font-family: "Lexend Mega", sans-serif;
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.05em;
    color: var(--color-text);
    line-height: 1.1;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .meta {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: 1.75rem;
  }

  .intro {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    border-left: 4px solid var(--color-primary);
    padding-left: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }

  .section {
    margin-bottom: 2.25rem;
  }

  .section-heading {
    font-family: "Lexend Mega", sans-serif;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    color: var(--color-text);
    border-left: 4px solid var(--color-primary);
    padding-left: 0.75rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.875rem;
  }

  .section p {
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .section p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .section ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0.5rem 0 0.75rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.5rem;
  }

  .section ul li {
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--color-text);
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    position: relative;
  }

  .section ul li::before {
    content: "—";
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  .contact-card {
    background-color: var(--color-bg);
    border: var(--border-width) solid var(--color-outline);
    border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-offset) var(--shadow-offset) 0 0
      var(--color-shadow);
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
    margin: 1rem 0;
    display: inline-block;
  }

  .contact-card p {
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem !important;
  }

  .contact-card p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0 !important;
  }

  .contact-link {
    color: var(--color-text);
    font-weight: 700;
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
    transition: color 0.15s ease;
  }

  .contact-link:hover {
    color: var(--color-coral);
  }

  .contact-link:focus-visible {
    outline: 3px solid var(--color-accent);
    outline-offset: 2px;
    border-radius: 2px;
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .page {
      padding: 1.5rem 1rem 3rem;
    }

    .card {
      padding: 2rem 1.5rem;
      transform: none;
    }
  }

  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
    .btn-back,
    .contact-link {
      transition: none;
    }
  }
</style>
